1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the concept of secrecy capacity, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the application of physical layer security in free-space optical communication systems, which is a topic of interest in the field of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper deals with the issue of achieving secure communication over free-space optical links, which is a topic of interest in the field of cryptography and security. 
4. cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The paper discusses the impacts of fading and channel correlation on the average secrecy capacity, which involves optimization and control of the communication system. 
5. cs.PH (Physics): The paper deals with the physical layer aspects of free-space optical communication systems, which is a topic of interest in the field of physics.
